1. Product Overview
ShelfSight is an AI-assisted library management system designed to streamline the process of cataloging, organizing, and managing physical libraries.
The system reduces manual cataloging by allowing librarians to upload images of book covers or spines, automatically extracting metadata and suggesting Dewey Decimal classifications.
In addition to standard library management features such as circulation and catalog management, ShelfSight connects the digital catalog to a visual representation of the physical library.
A custom 2D library map allows users to:
Browse shelf sections
Navigate the library visually
Locate books quickly through a spatial interface
The system also provides AI-generated organizational recommendations for shelf organization while ensuring that final decisions remain under librarian control.

