8. AI Ingestion Pipeline
Current implementation:
Step 1 — Upload: User uploads book image via POST /ingest/analyze (multipart form, field: image, max 10 MB).
Step 2 — Processing (Synchronous): Backend receives image in memory (Multer), sends to AWS Textract for OCR, detects ISBN from extracted text, enriches metadata via OpenAI, suggests Dewey Decimal classification.
Step 3 — Response: Returns OCR text, detected ISBN, suggested metadata, and Dewey classification to the frontend in a single response.
Planned architecture (async):
Step 2 — Job Creation: Backend stores image in AWS S3, creates IngestionJob record, sends job ID to SQS queue.
Step 3 — Async Processing: Worker (AWS Lambda, src/lambdas/ingest.handler.ts) consumes SQS event, retrieves image from S3, runs Textract OCR, detects ISBN, fetches metadata, suggests Dewey classification, updates IngestionJob record.
Step 4 — Review: Frontend polls job status. Staff reviews suggested data, edits fields if necessary, and approves or rejects. No catalog data is saved automatically.
Current status: The Lambda handler (ingest.handler.ts) is implemented but the SQS queue integration and job status polling endpoints (GET /ingest/jobs/:id, POST /ingest/jobs/:id/approve, POST /ingest/jobs/:id/reject) are not yet implemented in the Express routes. The current flow is synchronous via POST /ingest/analyze.

