13.1 Phase Gates
ShelfSight is built across 13 phases (see Section 11). Each phase has a gating rule:
Phases 1–4 (Foundation): Repo setup, API contract, authentication system, and CRUD APIs must be fully implemented and manually verified before any UI work begins.
Phases 5–7 (Core UI + Integration): Do NOT start connecting frontend to backend until the underlying API endpoints return correct responses when tested via curl or Postman. All circulation endpoints must pass before the circulation workflow phase.
Phases 8–10 (Map + AI): The shelf browsing UI, map prototype, and OCR pipeline depend on completed catalog and circulation features. Do not begin map or AI work until the catalog UI is fully connected to live API data.
Phases 11–13 (Polish + Deploy): Beta and deployment phases require all MVP features to be functional. Do not begin deployment until the Alpha milestone (Phase 9) passes end-to-end manual testing.
13.2 Build Order Within Each Feature
For every feature, build in this exact order:
Database schema (Prisma migration)
Backend route + controller + service
Backend manual verification (curl / Postman)
Frontend UI (page + components + hooks)
End-to-end verification (frontend → backend → database)
Complete each feature fully (backend + frontend + verification) before moving to the next feature in the same phase. After completing each feature, verify it satisfies every requirement ID listed for that feature before moving on.
